ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Got it! So you're using <strong>Next.js Pages Router</strong>.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The error <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">No Output Directory named "public" found</code> means <strong>Vercel is misconfigured</strong> — it's not detecting Next.js correctly.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h2 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">Fix: Update Vercel Project Settings</h2>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Go to your <strong>Vercel Dashboard → Your Project → Settings → General</strong> and set these:</p>
<div class="overflow-x-auto w-full px-2 mb-6"><table class="min-w-full border-collapse text-sm leading-[1.7] whitespace-normal"><thead class="text-left"><tr><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Setting</th><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Value</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><strong>Framework Preset</strong></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">Next.js</code></td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><strong>Build Command</strong></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">npm run build</code></td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><strong>Output Directory</strong></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Leave <strong>blank</strong> (Next.js manages this automatically)</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><strong>Install Command</strong></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">npm install</code></td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><strong>Root Directory</strong></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Leave <strong>blank</strong> (or set to folder where <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">package.json</code> is)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Then click <strong>Save</strong> and <strong>Redeploy</strong>.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h2 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">Also Add <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">vercel.json</code> to Your Project Root</h2>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Create a file called <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">vercel.json</code> in the same folder as your <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">package.json</code>:</p>
<div role="group" aria-label="json code" tabindex="0" class="relative group/copy bg-bg-000/50 border-0.5 border-border-400 rounded-lg focus:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-accent-100"><div class="sticky opacity-0 group-hover/copy:opacity-100 group-focus-within/copy:opacity-100 top-2 py-2 h-12 w-0 float-right"><div class="absolute right-0 h-8 px-2 items-center inline-flex z-10"><button class="inline-flex
  items-center
